@startuml Proposed Artifact Scanning Sequence (Milestone 1)

title Milestone 1 Architecture - Artifact Scanning with Abstractions

actor User
participant MainForm
participant ScanOrchestrator
participant ArtifactScraper
participant IScreenCapture
participant IImageProcessor
participant ScanProfile
participant IOcrEngine
participant "Progress<T>" as Progress
participant Inventory

User -> MainForm : Click "Scan"
activate MainForm

' Load configuration
MainForm -> ScanProfile : Load from ScanProfile.json
ScanProfile --> MainForm : Profiles loaded

' Detect resolution and select profile
MainForm -> IScreenCapture : GetGameWindowSize()
IScreenCapture --> MainForm : Size (e.g., 1600x900)

MainForm -> ScanProfile : GetProfile(aspectRatio: 1.778)
ScanProfile --> MainForm : ScanProfile (16:9)
note right: Dynamically selects profile based on aspect ratio

' Start orchestrated scan
MainForm -> ScanOrchestrator : ScanAllAsync(options, progress)
activate ScanOrchestrator

ScanOrchestrator -> ArtifactScraper : ScanArtifactsAsync(progress)
activate ArtifactScraper

' Navigate to artifact screen (async)
ArtifactScraper -> IScreenCapture : CaptureRegionAsync(countRegion)
activate IScreenCapture
IScreenCapture --> ArtifactScraper : IImage
deactivate IScreenCapture

ArtifactScraper -> IOcrEngine : Recognize(image, PageSegMode)
activate IOcrEngine
IOcrEngine --> ArtifactScraper : "895"
deactivate IOcrEngine
note right: Milestone 1: synchronous OCR\nCooperative cancellation via CancellationToken\nFull async/await is Milestone 2+

loop For each artifact (895)
  ' Report progress
  ArtifactScraper -> Progress : Report(new ScanProgress { Current=i, Total=895 })
  Progress --> MainForm : Update UI
  MainForm -> MainForm : UpdateProgressBar(i/895)

  ' Capture full artifact card (async)
  ArtifactScraper -> IScreenCapture : CaptureRegionAsync(cardRegion)
  note right: cardRegion from ScanProfile.Artifacts.Card
  activate IScreenCapture
  IScreenCapture --> ArtifactScraper : IImage card
  deactivate IScreenCapture

  ' Check for sanctified (async image processing)
  ArtifactScraper -> IImageProcessor : Crop(card, sanctifyIndicatorRegion)
  activate IImageProcessor
  note right: sanctifyIndicatorRegion from ScanProfile
  IImageProcessor --> ArtifactScraper : IImage indicator
  deactivate IImageProcessor

  ArtifactScraper -> IImageProcessor : GetPixel(indicator, center)
  IImageProcessor --> ArtifactScraper : Color(220, 192, 255)

  ArtifactScraper -> ArtifactScraper : IsPurple(color)
  note right: isPurple = (B>R>=G) && (B>150)

  alt Is Sanctified
    ArtifactScraper -> ScanProfile : Get substatsRegion + sanctifyShift
    ScanProfile --> ArtifactScraper : Rectangle {y: 0.4216 + 0.0520}
  else Regular artifact
    ArtifactScraper -> ScanProfile : Get substatsRegion
    ScanProfile --> ArtifactScraper : Rectangle {y: 0.4216}
  end

  ' Crop all regions (parallel processing possible)
  par Parallel region extraction
    ArtifactScraper -> IImageProcessor : Crop(card, nameRegion)
    IImageProcessor --> ArtifactScraper : IImage nameImg
  and
    ArtifactScraper -> IImageProcessor : Crop(card, substatsRegion)
    IImageProcessor --> ArtifactScraper : IImage substatsImg
  and
    ArtifactScraper -> IImageProcessor : Crop(card, levelRegion)
    IImageProcessor --> ArtifactScraper : IImage levelImg
  end

  ' OCR processing (async, with timeout)
  ArtifactScraper -> IOcrEngine : Recognize(nameImg)
  activate IOcrEngine
  note right: Async with CancellationToken (30s timeout)

  alt OCR completes within timeout
    IOcrEngine --> ArtifactScraper : OcrResult("Cinder City Sands")
    deactivate IOcrEngine
  else OCR times out
    IOcrEngine --> ArtifactScraper : TaskCanceledException
    deactivate IOcrEngine
    ArtifactScraper -> Progress : Report(new Error { Id=i, Message="OCR timeout" })
    note right: Continues to next artifact instead of crashing
  end

  ' Parse OCR results into artifact
  ArtifactScraper -> ArtifactScraper : ParseArtifact(ocrResults)
  ArtifactScraper -> ArtifactScraper : artifact = new Artifact { ... }

  ' Validation
  alt artifact.IsValid()
    ArtifactScraper -> Inventory : Add(artifact)
    note right: Thread-safe collection
  else Invalid
    ArtifactScraper -> Progress : Report(new Error { ... })
    ArtifactScraper -> ArtifactScraper : SaveDebugData(artifact, images)
  end

  ' Clean up images
  ArtifactScraper -> ArtifactScraper : DisposeImages(card, nameImg, substatsImg, ...)
  note right: IImage.Dispose() releases ImageSharp resources

  ' Navigate to next (async input)
  ArtifactScraper -> IScreenCapture : ScrollDownAsync()
end

ArtifactScraper --> ScanOrchestrator : List<Artifact>
deactivate ArtifactScraper

' Optionally scan other categories
ScanOrchestrator -> ScanOrchestrator : ScanWeaponsAsync()
ScanOrchestrator -> ScanOrchestrator : ScanCharactersAsync()

ScanOrchestrator -> Inventory : Build final inventory
ScanOrchestrator --> MainForm : Inventory complete
deactivate ScanOrchestrator

' Export to GOOD format
MainForm -> GOOD : Export(inventory)
GOOD --> MainForm : JSON string

MainForm -> MainForm : SaveToFile(json)
MainForm --> User : Show "Scan Complete"
deactivate MainForm

note over IScreenCapture, IOcrEngine
  **Improvements over Current:**
  1. All operations async (no thread blocking)
  2. IScreenCapture abstraction (platform-agnostic)
  3. IImageProcessor abstraction (ImageSharp, cross-platform)
  4. IOcrEngine abstraction (testable, swappable)
  5. ScanProfile (external config, no hard-coded coordinates)
  6. IProgress<T> (proper progress reporting)
  7. Timeout handling via CancellationToken (cleaner than Task.WhenAny)
  8. Resource cleanup with IDisposable pattern
end note

note over ArtifactScraper, ScanProfile
  **External Configuration Benefits:**
  - ScanProfile loaded from JSON at runtime
  - No recompilation to support new resolutions
  - Users can create custom profiles
  - Steam Deck, 4K, ultrawide all configurable
end note

note over MainForm
  **Testability:**
  Can inject MockScreenCapture and MockOcrEngine
  for unit testing without actual game running.

  Test example:
  var mockCapture = new MockScreenCapture("./testdata/");
  var scraper = new ArtifactScraper(mockCapture, ...);
  var artifacts = await scraper.ScanArtifactsAsync();
  Assert.Equal(5, artifacts.Count);
end note

@enduml
